1. SEC Acting Chairman Mark Uyeda hinted that a "regulatory sandbox" model will be adopted for companies trading tokenized securities;
2. TRUMP will usher in a large-scale unlocking, and there are 12,000 addresses with holdings exceeding $1,000;
3. SEC and Binance have jointly applied to the court for a 60-day suspension of litigation;
4. WSJ: Binance hopes that the United States will relax its supervision of the platform and is exploring the possibility of cooperating with Trump WLFI;
5. A US judge ruled that DCG's suspected fraud-related cases can enter the trial stage;
6. Meteora launched DAMM V2 and plans to deploy it to the main application in the next few weeks;
7. Solana Meme token BANG's market value briefly exceeded $15 million, with a 24-hour increase of about 3,000 times;
8. Arthur Hayes: Bitcoin is expected to enter a mode of only rising and not falling;
9. Ansem: If SOL can stand firm at $120 on a weekly basis, it is expected to see a radical rebound for several consecutive weeks.
